        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43753",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Interesting find!  I've attached a patch which reproduces the issue, and a possible fix.  Essentially I updated Zend_Loader_Autoloader_Resource::setOptions to shift the 'namespace' key to the beginning of the array, so that it is processed first.  This should be a more robust solution than sorting the keys.  Comments?\r\n{code}\r\n\/\/ If namespace key exists, shift it to be beginning of the options array\r\n\/\/ so that it is processed first\r\n\/\/ @see ZF-10836\r\n$namespaceIndex = array_search('namespace', array_keys($options));\r\nif ( $namespaceIndex !== false )\r\n{\r\n    $namespace = $options['namespace'];\r\n    unset($options['namespace']);\r\n    $options = array('namespace'=>$namespace) + $options;\r\n}\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-19T16:25:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-19T16:25:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43754",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Adam\r\nI think that could be but simple\r\n{code}\r\nif (array_key_exists('namespace', $options)) {\r\n    $this->setNamespace($options['namespace']);\r\n    unset($options['namespace']);\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThanks advance",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-19T16:30:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-19T16:30:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43755",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Ramon\r\nThanks! That is much simpler.  I've updated my patch with your code.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-19T16:35:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-19T16:35:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
